BY IFEOMA IKEM
THE Ikeja City Mall announced the 4th edition of its annual fashion on August 4th.
The theme “Catwalk in ICM” will showcase the spring summer 2016/ 2017 collections from Mango, Da Viva, Woodin, Lacoste, Levi’s, Audacious, Ruff ‘n’ Tumble, Redtag, TM Lewin, Ennzo.
Other include casabella (Wigs), Mac ( Official makeup provider for models) and Bruno’s place (Male models grooming). The Market Manager of ICM, Mr. Eniola Ositelu said that with the 4th edition of the Cat Walk coming up our focus remains positioning the mall as the choice destination for shopping.
Ositelu further said that Catwalk in ICM remains our greatest platform and the launch pad of indigenous and international fashion brands sold at ICM. With over 40% of tenants in the mall in to fashion and fashion accessories
